Conditional Types

Conditional types select a type based on a condition, similar to a ternary expression but at the type level.

### Basic Syntax

```typescript
type IsString<T> = T extends string ? "yes" : "no";

type A = IsString<string>; // "yes"
type B = IsString<number>; // "no"
type C = IsString<boolean>; // "no"
```

### Type Inference with infer

The `infer` keyword allows you to extract a type from a conditional:

```typescript
type ReturnType<T> = T extends (...args: any[]) => infer R ? R : never;

type Fn = (a: number, b: string) => boolean;
type R = ReturnType<Fn>; // boolean
```

### Distributive Conditional Types

When a conditional type acts on a naked type parameter, it distributes over unions:

```typescript
type ToArray<T> = T extends unknown ? T[] : never;

type Result = ToArray<string | number>;
// string[] | number[] (distributed)

// Non-distributive version
type ToArrayNonDist<T> = [T] extends [unknown] ? T[] : never;
type Result2 = ToArrayNonDist<string | number>;
// (string | number)[]
```

### Practical Examples

```typescript
type IsNever<T> = [T] extends [never] ? true : false;

type ExtractStrings<T> = T extends string ? T : never;

type ExcludeNull<T> = T extends null | undefined ? never : T;

type NonNullable<T> = T extends null | undefined ? never : T;
```

### Chained Conditionals

```typescript
type TypeName<T> =
  T extends string ? "string" :
  T extends number ? "number" :
  T extends boolean ? "boolean" :
  T extends undefined ? "undefined" :
  T extends Function ? "function" :
  "object";

type T1 = TypeName<string>; // "string"
type T2 = TypeName<() => void>; // "function"
```

> **Key Point:** Conditional types enable type-level programming and are foundational for utility types.

codeExample:
// Extract element type from array
type ElementType<T> = T extends (infer U)[] ? U : never;

type E1 = ElementType<string[]>; // string
type E2 = ElementType<number[]>; // number
type E3 = ElementType<boolean>; // never

// Extract promise type
type Unwrap<T> = T extends Promise<infer U> ? U : T;

type P1 = Unwrap<Promise<string>>; // string
type P2 = Unwrap<number>; // number

// Recursive conditional type
type DeepReadonly<T> = {
  readonly [P in keyof T]: T[P] extends object
    ? DeepReadonly<T[P]>
    : T[P];
};
